function minTimeToType(word) {
    let time = 0, prev = 0;
    for (let c of word) {
        let pos = c.charCodeAt(0) - 'a'.charCodeAt(0);
        time += Math.min(Math.abs(pos - prev), 26 - Math.abs(pos - prev)) + 1;
        prev = pos;
    }
    return time;
}
```


    The algorithm calculates the minimum time to type the characters in the given word. We initialize time and previous character position to 0. We then loop through each character in the word and calculate their position in alphabet by subtracting 'a'.

To find the time to move the pointer from the previous character to the current character, we use the minimum of the absolute difference between the positions and 26 - absolute difference between positions (because at max distance is 13 letters). We add 1 to the total time because typing the character would take 1 second as well.

Update the previous position variable to the current character position and continue this process for all the characters in the word. The resulting total time is the minimum number of seconds required to type the given word.

